Virtual Special of the Day: Talented Tuesday! 🎓👏

Today, Talented Tuesday is for celebrating our TALENTED Kindergarten and Sixth Grade students who are officially GRADUATING today!!

Kindergarten will be graduating first. Check out the Kindergarten graduation slideshow here: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vSTI6Hm58yqRPY48PJ2idX_zFsrLXPe-zjsoDLHJFtHKjhwLqTrbIC7ICCTfRNuRvUfldQHCx1sqkkv/pub?start=true&loop=true&delayms=2000

If you are having trouble with the sound, hit the back arrow after the first slide and the music will begin.

Our Kindergarten graduation parade begins at 5pm. Please see the flyer below for additional details.

Sixth Grade families, our Sixth Grade graduation parade begins at 7pm. More details can be found in the flyer below. Their graduation slide show will be featured in their own post this afternoon at 3pm. Stay tuned!

We are so excited to celebrate this special milestone! 💙🐾

Cole Academy Families,

Following Gov. Gretchen Whitmer's, "Stay Home, Stay Safe" Executive Order, the front office at Cole Academy will be closed until April 13th. However, we are still here to help!

To contact the front office, please call Mrs. Jasonowicz at 616-710-1676. You may also email Mrs. Bishop at bishopa@coleacademy.org or Mrs. Jasonowicz at Jasonowicza@coleacademy.org. Teacher emails can also be found at www.coleacademy.org. Please do not hesitate to reach out!

We hope all our Cole Academy students and families are staying home and staying healthy. We look forward to seeing each and every student soon! 🐾💙

Cole Academy Families-

Last night, Governor Gretchen Whitmer and State Superintendent Michael Rice announced the closure of all Michigan K-12 school buildings, public, private and boarding, starting Monday, March 16 through Sunday, April 5. In addition, Cole Academy will remain closed for Spring Break through Sunday, April 12 with school resuming on Monday, April 13.

Students will not be able to enter schools after today and staff access will be restricted. If your child has medications or other essential items that they will need while away that are stored in the school office, please contact the office to arrange for those items to be collected.

Student work for the closure will be sent…

post_text: The first graders visited Sparrow Hospital on their field trip today. Students learned about hospital procedures during the hands-on program called “Hello Hospital”. They had the chance to explore the tools and equipment used in surgery, a laboratory, a Patient room, and an x-ray/casting room. They also learned about various hospital jobs. They had a great time and learned a lot!

Our 4th grade students went on a skiing field trip to Mt. Brighton. They had a blast learning the basics of skiing from instructors and then giving it a try on their own. They definitely showed perseverance!

Our kindergarten and 1st grade students (finally!) celebrated the 100th day of school. They celebrating by dressing up like they are 100 years old and completing 100th day challenges. They had to build a cup tower with 100 cups, make necklaces with 100 beads, build a structure using toothpicks and 100 marshmallows, put together a 100 piece puzzle, see how many licks it takes to get to the middle of a lollipop, and more!
text:
Yesterday was another busy day at Cole Academy!

Our 4th grade students went on a skiing field trip to Mt. Brighton. They had a blast learning the basics of skiing from instructors and then giving it a try on their own. They definitely showed perseverance!

Our kindergarten and 1st grade students (finally!) celebrated the 100th day of school. They celebrating by dressing up like they are 100 years old and completing 100th day challenges. They had to build a cup tower with 100 cups, make necklaces with 100 beads, build a structure using toothpicks and 100 marshmallows, put together a 100 piece puzzle, see how many licks it takes to get to the middle of a lollipop, and more!

post_text: The 1st graders have been working on reading aloud nonfiction books like an expert. For their reading celebration, they got to teach our kindergartners all about their nonfiction topics. These topics included animals, insects, weather, science, the ocean, and many more. It also inspired our kindergarten writers to write their own nonfiction about Lionni the gecko! Way to go, first grade readers!!
